              </m:mrow> 
</m:math>
 are not be equal. However, if the motion is along a straight line and without any change in direction (i.e unidirectional), then distance and displacement are equal and so magnitude of average velocity and average speed are equal. In the case of instantaneous velocity, the time interval is infinitesimally small for which displacement and distance are infinitesimally small. In such situation, both displacement and distance are same. Hence, magnitude of instantaneous velocity 
