              <m:mo>|</m:mo>
              <m:mi mathvariant="bold">v</m:mi>
              <m:mo>|</m:mo>
          </m:mtd>
          </m:mtr>
         </m:mtable> 
     </m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-77"><term>2: </term>  Since, speed is a scalar quantity, it can be plotted on a single axis. For this reason, tangent to distance – time curve gives the speed at that point of the motion. As 
<m:math>
